📄 Online Medication & Prescription Tracker
Project Documentation

1. Introduction

The Online Medication & Prescription Tracker is a full-stack web application designed to simplify medication management for patients and improve communication between doctors and patients. The system provides a centralized platform where users can manage prescriptions, track medications, and request refills digitally.

2. Problem Statement

In traditional healthcare systems, patients often face difficulties in managing their medications and remembering dosage schedules. Doctors also find it challenging to monitor patient adherence and update prescriptions efficiently. Manual processes for prescription handling and refill requests can lead to delays, errors, and poor communication between patients and healthcare providers.

Therefore, there is a need for a centralized digital solution that can streamline medication tracking, improve prescription management, and ensure better coordination between patients, doctors, and administrators.

3. Objectives

To help patients track their medications and schedules

To enable doctors to manage prescriptions efficiently

To reduce manual errors and delays in medication management

To provide a secure and centralized healthcare system

4. System Overview

The system connects three main users:

Admin – Manages the system and users

Doctor – Prescribes medicines and monitors patients

Patient – Tracks medications and requests refills

5. Technology Stack
Frontend

React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, React Router, TypeScript

Backend

Java, Spring Boot, REST APIs, LLaMA Model, Groq API

Database

MongoDB

Tools

VS Code, Git & GitHub, Postman

6. Key Features

Secure Authentication (JWT-based login, role-based access)

Medication Tracking (schedule and dosage tracking)

Prescription Management (doctor-managed prescriptions)

Refill Requests (online approval system)

AI Chatbot (smart responses using AI)

7. System Workflow

The workflow starts with user registration, followed by secure authentication. After login, users manage their profiles. Patients track medications, while doctors prescribe medicines and manage prescriptions efficiently through the system.

8. Database Design

Collections include Users, Medications, Prescriptions, and Refill Requests to manage all system data efficiently.

9. API Structure

Includes REST APIs for authentication, medication tracking, prescription creation, and refill management.

10. System Architecture

Three-layer architecture:

Frontend (React UI)

Backend (Spring Boot logic)

Database (MongoDB storage)

